The paper discusses the problem of scientific information overload and proposes an algorithm for extracting metadata directly from scientific articles. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with the organization and retrieval of information. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning algorithms, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also deals with digital libraries, which falls under the sub-category of Digital Libraries (cs.DL). Finally, the paper's focus on scientific literature and citation networks suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Cybernetics (cs.CY), which deals with the study of communication and control in complex systems.
